1. Create a comparison table listing at least 4 key differences between RADIUS and TACACS+ features, focusing on protocol type, encryption, ports used, and command authorization.
=>Feature               RADIUS                                                       TACACS+
Protocol Type     UDP (connectionless)                                  TCP (connection-oriented)
Encryption      Encrypts only the password in access-request packets       Encrypts the entire packet body
Ports Used         1812 (auth), 1813 (accounting)                         49 (all communications)
Command Authorization       Limited                          Granular per-command authorization (ideal for admin sessions)1.

