3. Describe a real-world scenario from any app you use (such as Zomato, Paytm, or IRCTC) where TACACS+ would be more suitable than RADIUS for managing admin access, and explain why.
=>In IRCTC (or similar government/enterprise admin panels), network admins managing core routers/switches for the booking system would benefit from TACACS+.
Why more suitable than RADIUS: TACACS+ provides granular command-level authorization (e.g., allow "show running-config" but deny "configure terminal" for junior admins) and full packet encryption. This is critical for auditing privileged access to sensitive infrastructure handling millions of user transactions and PII. RADIUS is weaker for admin sessions as it combines auth/authz less flexibly and encrypts less. TACACS+ centralizes admin AAA while separating it from end-user auth.

4. List two advantages and two disadvantages of using RADIUS for network authentication in a public hotspot (like those found in malls or airports).
=>Advantages:

Lightweight and widely supported by access points and client devices (easy 802.1X deployment).
Good for centralized user authentication and accounting (tracks usage for fair access or billing).

Disadvantages:

Limited encryption (only password) makes it vulnerable to eavesdropping in public environments.
UDP-based, so less reliable for critical sessions; lacks strong per-command control for any admin functions.

